headline: Weyerhaeuser beats first quarter profit estimates on strong domestic demand
summary: According to U.S. government data released on Wednesday new home sales surged to a six-month high in March, as buyers hurried to capitalize on declining mortgage rates, benefiting firms like Weyerhaeuser which supply lumber for new home construction.  Last year, Weyerhaeuser acquired 84,300 acres of timberlands in Alabama through three transactions totaling $244 million.  The company's Timberlands segment reported quarterly adjusted core profit of $167 million for the January-March quarter, up 16% from a year earlier.

headline: Weyerhaeuser: Q1 Earnings Snapshot
summary: SEATTLE (AP) — Weyerhaeuser Co. (WY) on Thursday reported first-quarter earnings of $83 million. The Seattle-based company said it had net income of 11 cents per share. The results met Wall Street expectations.
